# Azveria Online Admin Guide

This document defines admin-only behavior in the Azveria Online web app.

## Admin Navigation

### Announcements
- View global announcement history.
- Send new global announcements.
- Player accounts can read but cannot post.

### All Nations
- Right panel nation selector + search.
- Center panel editable nation state.
- Save: commits changes to selected nation.
- Cancel: reverts unsaved values to snapshot from select-time.
- Supports creating placeholder (dummy) nations with full editable stats.

### Map
- View and pan/zoom all map layers.
- Upload replacement images for:
	- Main map
	- Terrain map
	- Political map
- Changes are global and instantly visible to all users.

### Chat
- Access all chats.
- Create/delete group chats.
- Add/remove members in group chats.
- Direct message any player.

### Shop
- Manage categories:
	- Refinement
	- Upgrades
	- Recruitment
	- Crafting
- Edit item cost/effect definitions.
- Save persists changes globally for all players.

### Help Dropdown
- About (website version + game version + metadata)
- Documentation (opens admin readme)
- Logout

## API Permission Boundaries
- Admin has full CRUD on nations, map layers, shop catalog, and chat membership.
- Player has self-scope write access only (nation about/settings and player actions).

## Realtime
WebSocket channels are used for:
- Announcements broadcast
- Chat messages/presence

Admin mutation endpoints still go through Laravel REST APIs, then broadcast via websocket where relevant.

## Audit and Safety Notes
- Every admin save operation should produce an audit record with:
	- actor user id
	- target table/entity
	- before/after payload diff
	- timestamp
- Use optimistic locking for nation/shop edits to avoid overwriting concurrent admin updates.

